You could achieve this using a simple bash function actually. For example, adding something like this to your `.bashrc` or `.bash_profile`:

```bash
function kgcomp() {
    kaggle competitions ${@:1:1} -c jigsaw-toxic-comment-classification-challenge ${@:2}
}
```

Running:  
`kgcomp submit -f submission.csv -d "description"`  
should then just be equivalent to:  
`kaggle competitions submit -c jigsaw-toxic-comment-classification-challenge -f submission.csv -d "description"`

